Key Match Events: Saud Shakeel scored a half-century against Netherlands in the ongoing ICC Men's Cricket World Cup 2023
Shakeel formed a crucial 120-run partnership with Mohammad Rizwan
Pre-Game Insights: Shakeel said he developed his game according to the team's needs
He was preferred over Salman Ali Agha in Pakistan's middle order for their opening match of the 2023 World Cup
Post-Match Reflections: Shakeel thanked the coaching staff and the crowd for supporting them at the Rajiv Gandhi Stadium in Hyderabad
He dedicated his performance to his coach
Miscellaneous Highlights: Pakistan beat Netherlands by 81 runs at the Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium in Hyderabad
Following the win, Pakistan will gear up to face Sri Lanka at the same venue on October 10
Others: Shakeel scored 68 runs off 52 balls, smashing nine boundaries and a solitary six
